    <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <span class="eyebrow">Cleaning work, made clearer</span>
          <h1>Cleaning jobs in New Zealand, made simple.</h1>
          <p class="lead">Apply once, complete the Spruce certification process, and become eligible for suitable residential and commercial cleaning work allocation.</p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apply/">Apply now
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
            </a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/how-it-works/">See how it works</a>
          </div>
          <div class="trust">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 3l7 3v6c0 4.5-3 7.5-7 9-4-1.5-7-4.5-7-9V6l7-3z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
            <span>Connected to the Spruce standard. Applications reviewed before onboarding.</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="app-card" aria-label="Application summary">
          <div class="app-card-head">
            <div>
              <div class="t">Your application</div>
              <div class="s">Five clear steps</div>
            </div>
            <span class="badge"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> Open</span>
          </div>
          <ol>
            <li><span class="stp">1</span><div><span class="ttl">Apply online</span><span class="det">A short form — takes a few minutes.</span></div></li>
            <li><span class="stp">2</span><div><span class="ttl">We review your application</span><span class="det">Applications are reviewed individually.</span></div></li>
            <li><span class="stp">3</span><div><span class="ttl">Complete verification</span><span class="det">Right-to-work and basic checks.</span></div></li>
            <li><span class="stp">4</span><div><span class="ttl">Train or certify to the Spruce standard</span><span class="det">Short training or assessment.</span></div></li>
            <li><span class="stp">5</span><div><span class="ttl">Eligible for work allocation</span><span class="det">Matched by location, suitability, and demand.</span></div></li>
          </ol>
          <div class="app-card-foot">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 8v4l3 2M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
            <span>Apply once. We&rsquo;ll keep your details on file.</span>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== WHY APPLY — split with benefit rows ===== -->
    <section class="block tint" id="why">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="why-split">
          <div class="why-left">
            <span class="eyebrow">Why Cleaning Jobs</span>
            <h2>A clearer way into Spruce cleaning work.</h2>
            <p>Cleaning Jobs gives suitable cleaners one place to apply for Spruce-standard cleaning work. Instead of applying role by role, applicants can be reviewed once and considered for suitable work based on location, demand, availability, certification, and fit.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="why-panel">
            <div class="why-rows">
              <div class="why-row">
                <span class="n">01</span>
                <div>
                  <h3>One place to apply</h3>
                  <p>Your details stay on file so you do not need to re-apply for every suitable role.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="why-row">
                <span class="n">02</span>
                <div>
                  <h3>Spruce network behind it</h3>
                  <p>Cleaning Jobs is connected to Spruce residential, commercial, and specialist cleaning work.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="why-row">
                <span class="n">03</span>
                <div>
                  <h3>Standards before allocation</h3>
                  <p>Suitable cleaners know the expectations before work is allocated.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="why-row">
                <span class="n">04</span>
                <div>
                  <h3>Matched to suitable work</h3>
                  <p>Work is considered based on location, demand, suitability, availability, and certification.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== RELIABLE — split with tick list ===== -->
    <section class="block" id="who">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="reliable-split">
          <div class="reliable-left">
            <span class="eyebrow">What we look for</span>
            <h2>Reliable people do well here.</h2>
