    <!-- ===== FAQ ===== -->
    <section class="block faq-block" id="faq">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <span class="eyebrow">Frequently asked questions</span>
          <h2>Things people ask before applying</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Do I need cleaning experience?
              <span class="ico" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="answer"><p>Experience is preferred but not always required. Reliability, attention to detail, and willingness to follow checklists matter just as much. The Spruce certification process is there to bring you up to speed.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Is work guaranteed?
              <span class="ico" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="answer"><p>No. We don&rsquo;t guarantee a minimum number of jobs. Work depends on location, demand, availability, suitability, and certification. What we offer is a clear, structured process for becoming eligible for it.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Do I need my own transport?
              <span class="ico" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="answer"><p>Transport is often preferred, especially for residential work spread across an area. Some commercial roles may be accessible by public transport. We&rsquo;ll ask about your situation in the application.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Do I need my own equipment?
              <span class="ico" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="answer"><p>It depends on the type of work. Residential cleans often require basic equipment; commercial sites frequently supply their own. The specifics are covered during onboarding.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Can teams apply?
              <span class="ico" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="answer"><p>Yes. You can apply as an individual, a small team, or a cleaning partnership. There&rsquo;s an option to indicate this in the application.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Is this employment or contractor work?
              <span class="ico" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="answer"><p>The working arrangement varies by role and is confirmed during onboarding. We&rsquo;ll be clear about the arrangement before any work is allocated to you.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What areas are available?
              <span class="ico" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="answer"><p>Recruitment is demand-led, so availability depends on where there&rsquo;s current demand for work. Apply with your location and we&rsquo;ll let you know if there&rsquo;s a suitable next step in your area.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What is Spruce certification?
              <span class="ico" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="answer"><p>A short training or assessment against the Spruce standard. It ensures everyone working in the network delivers a consistent quality of clean, with clear checklists and shared expectations.</p></div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How long does onboarding take?
              <span class="ico" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="answer"><p>It depends on your experience, availability, and the work types you&rsquo;re applying for. We&rsquo;ll give you an indication after reviewing your application.</p></div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

